details:
The AIR program is a great way for students to connect with alumni and ask all of those questions you do not have time or feel comfortable asking at career fairs and informational interview. Drop by this informal space and visit alumni and Public Service Center to ask questions you might have about:
·Applying your student service experiences to serving communities post-graduation;
·How to land that first public service position;
·Work-life balance outside of Cal;
·Your own current job search including resume or cover letters; and
·Other questions you might have related to careers and life after Cal!

Meng So, 2010 (M.Ed from UCLA)
Currently working with: UC Berkeley Undocumented Student Program Coordinator; also has worked as a seminar instructor in Summer Bridge.
Meng is a past participant and leader with the BUILD, Bonner Leaders AmeriCorps, and Alternative Breaks programs, and was a member of the Social Justice Conference Planning team.
Event Contact: publicservice@berkeley.edu, 510-642-3916
